        <hr noshade size="2" color="#545A7D">
        
         I have to agree, EQ was a good game. It was revolutionary in a way that no other game has been able to touch. It took such a stranglehold on the market so quickly, no other gaming platform ever came close to scratching it. But, Verant has made some extremely poor decisions, and have created quite a mire for themselves. The high end game is spinning totally off kilter, without much hope of ever being rectified. Though I am not on a PVP server, everything I have heard and read about shows me that that environment is totally unbalanced as well. </P><P>At the end of the day, it is my opionion that Verant has really butchered things, especially for the character I chose to play. As such, I will NEVER, and I repeat NEVER touch another prooduct that has anything to do with Verant.</P><P>There are a couple gaming platforms I have been following with a great deal of interest:</P><P>Shadowbane. <a href="http://shadowbane.ubisoft.com/home/news.shtml" target="_blank">http://shadowbane.ubisoft.com/home/news.shtml</a> It is in beta testing currently. It has encountered a few delays, but is something that I am keenly watching.</P><P>Horizons. <a href="http://www.artifact-entertainment.com/horizons/home.htm" target="_blank">http://www.artifact-entertainment.com/horizons/home.htm</a> This one I had kept an eye on a while back, but it had seemed to enter the Vapor Ware state. Apparently, it is back in development. It disapointed me to see that it they seem to have gotten rid of the Vampire race, but still a platform that has some interesting ideas.</P><P>Though I have not been following it, Blizzard has some sort of online version of Warcraft pending I believe. In terms of customer service and thouroughness of testing, few gaming companies have received higher praise then Blizzard.</P><P></P><P>Cheers,<BR><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=63522">Ancagalon the Black </a><BR>Warlock - Terris Thule<BR><a href="#top"><img src="icon_go_up.gif" height="15" wi