         Hello folks,</P><P>I agree with allot stated here.  I'll try not to go off on one of my long posts again, *grin*, but. . .</P><P>Way back when, EQ really was a dream come true.  As much as I bash it now, that's not so easy to admit to, but I hung on it like I was literally enchanted.  Heck! I remember watching a video, and thinking it was SO cool that you could sit down! *laughs*.</P><P>Of course, I didn't know that there would be zones and a whole lot of other silly limitations, either, but I s'pose that's beside the point.</P><P>Yeah well, back then, there wasn't really a 3D online fantasy game, and me being a fantasy buff, this was just totally awsome.</P><P>In short, I agree that Varant has torn it apart.  A small company that got REALLY big, their egos swelled, and became too affraid to change it. That, combined with allot of other factors (nerfs, refusal to fix glaring bugs instead of adding content, et al) acted, more or less, like rust on what was once a very pretty, shiny thing.</P><P>To continue with the metaphore, it's now nothing more than a rusted old bucket and it's just impossible to enjoy any more.  I miss... really miss certain people.  I can't justify the game or supporting the company though when my money really does need to go else where, and they simply don't deserve it.</P><P>That's my view on things.  Bye bye EQ!  They've built up a track record in the <i>years</i> that I was with them, and considering that record somebody's going to have to be really persuasive to get me to buy another one of their products.  Or Sigil Games, for that matter.</P><P>For reference, I cancelled a month prior to Sept. 10th or 11th of this year, I can't remember which day it was.  My access ran out on said day, though. Long before the exp and resistance changes.</P><P>Now, hm, as for. . . </P><P><BLOCKQUOTE id=quote><font size=2 face="Verdana" id=quote>quote:<hr height=1 noshade id=quote>I myself am waiting for the elusive Shadowbane.....but more than likely with just be vaporware. I don't think I'll be going to EQ2 but who knows what they will be playing in a years time.<hr height=1 noshade id=quote></BLOCKQUOTE id=quote></font id=quote><font face="Verdana" size=2 id=quote></P><P>Ya know that I can't say anything, all I can really say is.. nothing.  I will mention, however, that it's sitting on my hard drive and it is by FAR <b>not</b> vaporware.  . . . Don't lose hope, eh?  Personally, I think you're really going to like it if you're into whacking other players.  Just keep a down to Earth view of it, as one should of every MMOG.</P><P>I don't think that should break the NDA.</P><P>Have a nice day folks!</P><P>~Mysk</P><P>Additional EDIT:</P><P>I forgot to mention something on par with the Subject of this thread.  I'm thinking of Earth & Beyond (<a href="http://www.myskyra.net/ebmysk.shtml" target="_blank">http://www.myskyra.net/ebmysk.shtml</a>) for something different, or, WoW, or Final Fantasy Online (I am a HUGE Final Fantasy fanatic).</P><P><a href="http://www.myskyra.net/" target="_blank"><img src="http://www.myskyra.net/outside_images/logo.jpg" border=0></a><BR>-<BR><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=294911" target="_blank">http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=294911</a></P><P>Edited by - Mysk on 10/02/2002  22:42:21<a href="#top"><img src="icon_go_up.gif" height="15" width="15" border="0" align="right" alt="Go to Top of Page"></a></font></td>
